[2026-03-13T14:38:52Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016J3FikgezAeyZUjhJiSdbN","type":"tool_result","content":"# Cloche System Design\n\n## Overview\n\nCloche is a system for grow-coding high quality applications. It provides containerized\nenvironments for coding agents to operate in isolation, a workflow DSL for linking\nagentic and script-driven tasks, validated code pipelines, and self-evolving tooling.\n\nThis document describes the architecture for the MVP (v0.1).\n\n## System Components\n\nCloche is a Go monorepo producing three binaries:\n\n```\ncmd/\n  cloche/         # CLI client (short-lived)\n  cloched/        # Daemon/orchestrator (long-running)\n  cloche-agent/   # In-container entrypoint (autonomous)\n```\n\n### cloche (CLI)\n\nShort-lived process. Talks to `cloched` over gRPC (Unix socket locally, TCP remotely).\n\nSubcommands:\n- `run <workflow>` — Launch a new workflow run\n- `status [run-id]` — Check run status\n- `logs <run-id>` — Stream logs from a running workflow (bidirectional gRPC stream)\n- `stop <run-id>` — Cancel a running workflow (signals container with SIGTERM)\n---\n# Design: `cloche init`\n\n## Purpose\n\nScaffold a Cloche project in the current directory so a user can go from\nzero to `cloche run` with minimal setup.\n\n## CLI Interface\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--image <base-image>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow` | `develop` | Workflow name; creates `<name>.cloche` |\n| `--image` | `ubuntu:24.04` | Base Docker image for Dockerfile |\n\nNo flags required. Bare `cloche init` works with sensible defaults.\n\n## Generated Files\n\n```\n.\n├── <workflow>.cloche\n├── Dockerfile\n└── prompts/\n    ├── implement.md\n    └── fix.md\n```","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017xCxwq7vtimYnzVCvKMfnj","session_id":"aeb114c6-22ff-4078-baec-d21a69457fa7","uuid":"ac9e1b29-e88e-4365-928d-269da66bcb55"}
