[2026-03-13T14:38:52Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017xCxwq7vtimYnzVCvKMfnj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the documentation structure. Let me compile my findings.\n\n## Documentation Structure and Configuration Exploration Report\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche project's documentation and agent configuration. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Existing Documentation Structure**\n\n**Main User-Facing Docs** (in `/workspace/docs/`):\n- `/workspace/README.md` — High-level overview, quick start, and feature summary\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md` — Installation methods (build from source, `go install`, pre-built binaries planned, Homebrew planned)\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` — CLI reference, project layout, workflow DSL, configuration, and Dockerfile requirements\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` — Detailed workflow DSL syntax, execution model, host workflow examples\n\n**Design/Implementation Docs** (in `/workspace/docs/plans/`):\n- 20+ dated design and implementation documents following a consistent naming convention: `YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>-<design|implementation>.md`\n- Examples: `2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`, `2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md`, `2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n- These are architectural/design docs, not user-facing getting-started guides\n\n**Example Project** (in `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/`):\n- `README.md` demonstrating a complete Cloche workflow that built a Ruby calculator\n- Shows actual execution traces and artifact structure\n\n### 2. **Documentation Conventions**\n\nThe project uses:\n- **Markdown format** for all documentation (`.md` files)\n- **Clear sectioning** with `## Heading` hierarchy\n- **Code blocks** with syntax highlighting (go, bash, dockerfile, etc.)\n- **Tables** for reference material (flags, config options, environment variables)\n- **Structured examples** showing DSL syntax, commands, and expected output\n- **Consistent terminology** (workflow, step, result, wiring, agent adapter, etc.)\n- **Design-doc convention**: Dated planning documents stored separately from user docs\n\n### 3. **Agent-Related Documentation and Configuration**\n\n**Documented Agent Concepts**:\n- Agent adapters are pluggable implementations of the `AgentAdapter` interface\n- Known agents mentioned: `claude`, `gemini`, `codex` (in USAGE.md as fallback chain example)\n- Default agent is `claude` with specific default args: `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n- Fallback chains supported: `agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"` tries in order\n\n**Agent Configuration Points**:\n1. **Step-level config** (highest priority):\n   - `agent_command`: Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback\n   - `agent_args`: Override default arguments\n\n2. **Workflow-level config blocks**:\n   - `container { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }` for container workflows\n   - `host { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }` for host workflows\n\n3. **Environment variables**:\n   - `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`: Fallback if no config specified\n   - `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`: Passed through to containers for agent API calls\n\n**In Code** (agent adapters):\n- Located: `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/`\n- **Prompt adapter** (`prompt/`): Handles agent step execution with fallback chains\n- **Generic adapter** (`generic/`): Runs shell commands (script steps)\n- **Agent instantiation** happens in `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` and `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n\n### 4. **Container Configuration**\n\n**Dockerfile Location**: `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile`\n\n**Current Project's Dockerfile**:\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nCOPY --from=golang:1.25 /usr/local/go /usr/local/go\nENV PATH=\"/usr/local/go/bin:${PATH}\"\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nodejs npm\nRUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Base Image Requirements** (cloche-base:latest must include):\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- `agent` user (cloche runs commands as this user)\n- `/workspace` as working directory\n- Base system packages and utilities\n\n**Dockerfile Customization Pattern**:\n- Start with `FROM cloche-base:latest`\n- Add language runtimes and package managers\n- Install build dependencies\n- Install agent binary if needed (claude-code installed via npm)\n\n### 5. **Project Layout Convention**\n\n```\n.cloche/\n├── develop.cloche           # Container workflow (can have any name)\n├── host.cloche              # Host orchestration workflow\n├── Dockerfile               # Container image definition\n├── config.toml              # Project configuration\n├── prompts/                 # Prompt templates for agent steps\n│   ├── implement.md\n│   ├── fix.md\n│   └── update-docs.md\n├── scripts/                 # Host-side scripts (sh/bash)\n│   ├── prepare-prompt.sh\n│   ├── ready-tasks.sh\n│   ├── claim-task.sh\n│   ├── merge-to-main.sh\n│   └── cleanup-run.sh\n├── overrides/               # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n│   └── CLAUDE.md (optional) # Container-specific version of CLAUDE.md\n├── evolution/               # Self-evolution snapshots and knowledge base\n├── output/                  # Step logs and validation output\n├── attempt_count/           # Retry counters (runtime)\n└── <run-id>/                # Per-run state (gitignored)\n    ├── prompt.txt\n    ├── context.json\n    ├── output/\n    ├── attempt_count/\n    └── history.log\n```\n\n### 6. **Prompt Template Examples**\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/.cloche/prompts/`\n\n**Files in Project**:\n- `implement.md` — Agent writes initial implementation\n- `fix.md` — Agent fixes test/validation failures\n- `update-docs.md` — Agent synchronizes documentation with code\n\n**Template Structure**:\n- Markdown format with clear instructions\n- Guidelines section for best practices\n- Directives about validation requirements (e.g., \"MUST run tests before reporting success\")\n- Learned rules section documenting previous issues/resolutions\n\n### 7. **Missing Documentation / Gaps**\n\n**Not Found** (but referenced or implied):\n- No dedicated \"Getting Started with Agents\" guide\n- No \"How to Configure a Custom Agent\" tutorial\n- No detailed explanation of the `AgentAdapter` interface for developers\n- No troubleshooting guide for agent failures\n- No documentation on agent fallback chain behavior in practice\n- No examples of integrating alternative agents (Gemini, Codex, etc.)\n\n### 8. **Code Organization for Agent Support**\n\n**Agent Adapter Interface** (source: `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`):\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Known Adapters**:\n1. **Prompt Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`) — Invokes external agents (claude, gemini, etc.)\n2. **Generic Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/`) — Runs shell commands\n\n**Agent Resolution Flow** (from runner code):\n1. Check step-level `agent_command`\n2. Check workflow-level config block (`container.agent_command` or `host.agent_command`)\n3. Check `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default to `\"claude\"`\n5. Parse as comma-separated fallback chain\n6. Apply default args for known agents, or pass prompt on stdin for unknown agents\n\n### 9. **Configuration File Structure**\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml`\n\n**Current Content**:\n```toml\nactive = true\n\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 3\nstagger_seconds = 5.0\ndedup_seconds = 300\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = false\ndebounce_seconds = 30\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings Summary\n\n1. **Well-documented** — User-facing docs are comprehensive with examples and CLI reference\n2. **Design-heavy** — Many architectural design docs but limited getting-started guides\n3. **Agent-agnostic by design** — System supports pluggable agents via adapter pattern\n4. **Claude-first default** — \"claude\" is the default agent with predefined arguments\n5. **Fallback chains supported** — Agents can be chained with comma-separated syntax\n6. **Prompt templates are Markdown** — Easy for humans to read and agents to modify\n7. **Host vs. Container workflows clearly separated** — Different execution models, different config blocks\n8. **Evolution system planned** — Configuration exists for self-evolution but marked disabled\n9. **No agent-specific getting-started docs** — Gap in documentation for understanding agent configuration and customization\n\nAll absolute file paths referenced above are accurate and current as of the latest git status."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a533f918af8cde7d7 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57400\ntool_uses: 46\nduration_ms: 114165</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aeb114c6-22ff-4078-baec-d21a69457fa7","uuid":"c0423fad-a63d-4def-b6f7-ca8c8e681a01","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the documentation structure of this project. I need to understand:\n1. What docs already exist (especially setup/getting-started docs)\n2. The conventions used for documentation (format, style, location)\n3. Any existing agent-related documentation\n4. How containers are configured (Dockerfile, .cloche directory)\n5. Any references to Claude or Codex agents in the codebase\n\nSearch thoroughly in docs/, CLAUDE.md, .cloche/, and any README files. Also look for any existing agent adapter code in internal/adapters/ that might inform how agents are configured.","agentId":"a533f918af8cde7d7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the documentation structure. Let me compile my findings.\n\n## Documentation Structure and Configuration Exploration Report\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche project's documentation and agent configuration. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Existing Documentation Structure**\n\n**Main User-Facing Docs** (in `/workspace/docs/`):\n- `/workspace/README.md` — High-level overview, quick start, and feature summary\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md` — Installation methods (build from source, `go install`, pre-built binaries planned, Homebrew planned)\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` — CLI reference, project layout, workflow DSL, configuration, and Dockerfile requirements\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` — Detailed workflow DSL syntax, execution model, host workflow examples\n\n**Design/Implementation Docs** (in `/workspace/docs/plans/`):\n- 20+ dated design and implementation documents following a consistent naming convention: `YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>-<design|implementation>.md`\n- Examples: `2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`, `2026-02-23-cloche-init-design.md`, `2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n- These are architectural/design docs, not user-facing getting-started guides\n\n**Example Project** (in `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/`):\n- `README.md` demonstrating a complete Cloche workflow that built a Ruby calculator\n- Shows actual execution traces and artifact structure\n\n### 2. **Documentation Conventions**\n\nThe project uses:\n- **Markdown format** for all documentation (`.md` files)\n- **Clear sectioning** with `## Heading` hierarchy\n- **Code blocks** with syntax highlighting (go, bash, dockerfile, etc.)\n- **Tables** for reference material (flags, config options, environment variables)\n- **Structured examples** showing DSL syntax, commands, and expected output\n- **Consistent terminology** (workflow, step, result, wiring, agent adapter, etc.)\n- **Design-doc convention**: Dated planning documents stored separately from user docs\n\n### 3. **Agent-Related Documentation and Configuration**\n\n**Documented Agent Concepts**:\n- Agent adapters are pluggable implementations of the `AgentAdapter` interface\n- Known agents mentioned: `claude`, `gemini`, `codex` (in USAGE.md as fallback chain example)\n- Default agent is `claude` with specific default args: `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n- Fallback chains supported: `agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"` tries in order\n\n**Agent Configuration Points**:\n1. **Step-level config** (highest priority):\n   - `agent_command`: Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback\n   - `agent_args`: Override default arguments\n\n2. **Workflow-level config blocks**:\n   - `container { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }` for container workflows\n   - `host { agent_command = \"...\", agent_args = \"...\" }` for host workflows\n\n3. **Environment variables**:\n   - `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND`: Fallback if no config specified\n   - `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`: Passed through to containers for agent API calls\n\n**In Code** (agent adapters):\n- Located: `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/`\n- **Prompt adapter** (`prompt/`): Handles agent step execution with fallback chains\n- **Generic adapter** (`generic/`): Runs shell commands (script steps)\n- **Agent instantiation** happens in `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` and `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n\n### 4. **Container Configuration**\n\n**Dockerfile Location**: `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile`\n\n**Current Project's Dockerfile**:\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\nCOPY --from=golang:1.25 /usr/local/go /usr/local/go\nENV PATH=\"/usr/local/go/bin:${PATH}\"\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y nodejs npm\nRUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\nUSER agent\n```\n\n**Base Image Requirements** (cloche-base:latest must include):\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- `agent` user (cloche runs commands as this user)\n- `/workspace` as working directory\n- Base system packages and utilities\n\n**Dockerfile Customization Pattern**:\n- Start with `FROM cloche-base:latest`\n- Add language runtimes and package managers\n- Install build dependencies\n- Install agent binary if needed (claude-code installed via npm)\n\n### 5. **Project Layout Convention**\n\n```\n.cloche/\n├── develop.cloche           # Container workflow (can have any name)\n├── host.cloche              # Host orchestration workflow\n├── Dockerfile               # Container image definition\n├── config.toml              # Project configuration\n├── prompts/                 # Prompt templates for agent steps\n│   ├── implement.md\n│   ├── fix.md\n│   └── update-docs.md\n├── scripts/                 # Host-side scripts (sh/bash)\n│   ├── prepare-prompt.sh\n│   ├── ready-tasks.sh\n│   ├── claim-task.sh\n│   ├── merge-to-main.sh\n│   └── cleanup-run.sh\n├── overrides/               # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n│   └── CLAUDE.md (optional) # Container-specific version of CLAUDE.md\n├── evolution/               # Self-evolution snapshots and knowledge base\n├── output/                  # Step logs and validation output\n├── attempt_count/           # Retry counters (runtime)\n└── <run-id>/                # Per-run state (gitignored)\n    ├── prompt.txt\n    ├── context.json\n    ├── output/\n    ├── attempt_count/\n    └── history.log\n```\n\n### 6. **Prompt Template Examples**\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/.cloche/prompts/`\n\n**Files in Project**:\n- `implement.md` — Agent writes initial implementation\n- `fix.md` — Agent fixes test/validation failures\n- `update-docs.md` — Agent synchronizes documentation with code\n\n**Template Structure**:\n- Markdown format with clear instructions\n- Guidelines section for best practices\n- Directives about validation requirements (e.g., \"MUST run tests before reporting success\")\n- Learned rules section documenting previous issues/resolutions\n\n### 7. **Missing Documentation / Gaps**\n\n**Not Found** (but referenced or implied):\n- No dedicated \"Getting Started with Agents\" guide\n- No \"How to Configure a Custom Agent\" tutorial\n- No detailed explanation of the `AgentAdapter` interface for developers\n- No troubleshooting guide for agent failures\n- No documentation on agent fallback chain behavior in practice\n- No examples of integrating alternative agents (Gemini, Codex, etc.)\n\n### 8. **Code Organization for Agent Support**\n\n**Agent Adapter Interface** (source: `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`):\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Known Adapters**:\n1. **Prompt Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`) — Invokes external agents (claude, gemini, etc.)\n2. **Generic Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/`) — Runs shell commands\n\n**Agent Resolution Flow** (from runner code):\n1. Check step-level `agent_command`\n2. Check workflow-level config block (`container.agent_command` or `host.agent_command`)\n3. Check `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default to `\"claude\"`\n5. Parse as comma-separated fallback chain\n6. Apply default args for known agents, or pass prompt on stdin for unknown agents\n\n### 9. **Configuration File Structure**\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml`\n\n**Current Content**:\n```toml\nactive = true\n\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 3\nstagger_seconds = 5.0\ndedup_seconds = 300\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = false\ndebounce_seconds = 30\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings Summary\n\n1. **Well-documented** — User-facing docs are comprehensive with examples and CLI reference\n2. **Design-heavy** — Many architectural design docs but limited getting-started guides\n3. **Agent-agnostic by design** — System supports pluggable agents via adapter pattern\n4. **Claude-first default** — \"claude\" is the default agent with predefined arguments\n5. **Fallback chains supported** — Agents can be chained with comma-separated syntax\n6. **Prompt templates are Markdown** — Easy for humans to read and agents to modify\n7. **Host vs. Container workflows clearly separated** — Different execution models, different config blocks\n8. **Evolution system planned** — Configuration exists for self-evolution but marked disabled\n9. **No agent-specific getting-started docs** — Gap in documentation for understanding agent configuration and customization\n\nAll absolute file paths referenced above are accurate and current as of the latest git status."}],"totalDurationMs":114165,"totalTokens":57400,"totalToolUseCount":46,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":670,"cache_read_input_tokens":54456,"output_tokens":2269,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":670},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
