[2026-03-13T14:41:35Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DZPmL3tsoFtzWs4FRYuAiC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# How to Set Up Claude Code\n     2→\n     3→This guide covers configuring Cloche containers to use\n     4→[Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code) as the coding agent.\n     5→\n     6→## Prerequisites\n     7→\n     8→- A working Cloche installation ([Installation guide](INSTALL.md))\n     9→- Claude Code installed on the host (`npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`)\n    10→- An active Claude Code session on the host (run `claude` once to authenticate)\n    11→\n    12→## How Authentication Works\n    13→\n    14→Cloche automatically copies your host's `~/.claude/` directory and `~/.claude.json`\n    15→file into each container at `/home/agent/.claude` and `/home/agent/.claude.json`. This\n    16→reuses your existing Claude Code session so containers authenticate without needing an\n    17→API key.\n    18→\n    19→The files are copied (not bind-mounted) so each container gets its own copy, avoiding\n    20→concurrent write conflicts when multiple runs execute in parallel.\n    21→\n    22→## Dockerfile\n    23→\n    24→Your `.cloche/Dockerfile` must install Claude Code via npm:\n    25→\n    26→```dockerfile\n    27→FROM cloche-base:latest\n    28→USER root\n    29→\n    30→# Install Node.js (required for Claude Code)\n    31→RUN apt-get update \\\n    32→    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs npm \\\n    33→    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    34→\n    35→# Install Claude Code\n    36→RUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    37→\n    38→# Add your project's build dependencies here\n    39→# RUN apt-get install -y ...\n    40→\n    41→USER agent\n    42→```\n    43→\n    44→## Workflow Configuration\n    45→\n    46→Claude is the default agent, so no explicit configuration is needed. These are\n    47→equivalent:\n    48→\n    49→```\n    50→// Implicit — claude is the default\n    51→step implement {\n    52→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    53→  results = [success, fail]\n    54→}\n    55→\n    56→// Explicit\n    57→step implement {\n    58→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    59→  agent_command = \"claude\"\n    60→  results = [success, fail]\n    61→}\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→Default arguments passed to Claude Code:\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\n    68→```\n    69→\n    70→Override with `agent_args` if needed:\n    71→\n    72→```\n    73→step implement {\n    74→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    75→  agent_args = \"-p --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n    76→  results = [success, fail]\n    77→}\n    78→```\n    79→\n    80→## Using an API Key Instead\n    81→\n    82→If you prefer to use an API key rather than session reuse, set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in\n    83→the daemon's environment. Cloche passes it into containers automatically:\n    84→\n    85→```bash\n    86→export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"sk-ant-...\"\n    87→cloched &\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→This works alongside session reuse — Claude Code will use the API key if no session\n    91→is available.\n    92→\n    93→## Verifying the Setup\n    94→\n    95→Run a quick test workflow:\n    96→\n    97→```bash\n    98→cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Print hello world\"\n    99→```\n   100→\n   101→Check logs to confirm Claude Code is executing:\n   102→\n   103→```bash\n   104→cloche logs <run-id>\n   105→```\n   106→\n   107→## Troubleshooting\n   108→\n   109→**Claude Code not found in container**: Make sure your Dockerfile installs\n   110→`@anthropic-ai/claude-code` via npm and that Node.js is available.\n   111→\n   112→**Authentication errors**: Run `claude` on the host to ensure your session is active.\n   113→Cloche copies `~/.claude/` at container creation time, so a stale or missing session\n   114→on the host means containers won't authenticate.\n   115→\n   116→**Permission errors on `~/.claude`**: Cloche runs `chown -R agent:agent` on the copied\n   117→auth files at container startup. If you see permission errors, check that your\n   118→Dockerfile does not override the entrypoint.\n   119→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ea6a4db-317b-4116-946b-dfa5f420f957","uuid":"e668d8d5-da9e-4e5e-b9bb-ce7c7748c448","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/agent-setup-claude.md","content":"# How to Set Up Claude Code\n\nThis guide covers configuring Cloche containers to use\n[Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code) as the coding agent.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- A working Cloche installation ([Installation guide](INSTALL.md))\n- Claude Code installed on the host (`npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`)\n- An active Claude Code session on the host (run `claude` once to authenticate)\n\n## How Authentication Works\n\nCloche automatically copies your host's `~/.claude/` directory and `~/.claude.json`\nfile into each container at `/home/agent/.claude` and `/home/agent/.claude.json`. This\nreuses your existing Claude Code session so containers authenticate without needing an\nAPI key.\n\nThe files are copied (not bind-mounted) so each container gets its own copy, avoiding\nconcurrent write conflicts when multiple runs execute in parallel.\n\n## Dockerfile\n\nYour `.cloche/Dockerfile` must install Claude Code via npm:\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM cloche-base:latest\nUSER root\n\n# Install Node.js (required for Claude Code)\nRUN apt-get update \\\n    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs npm \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install Claude Code\nRUN npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n\n# Add your project's build dependencies here\n# RUN apt-get install -y ...\n\nUSER agent\n```\n\n## Workflow Configuration\n\nClaude is the default agent, so no explicit configuration is needed. These are\nequivalent:\n\n```\n// Implicit — claude is the default\nstep implement {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n\n// Explicit\nstep implement {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  agent_command = \"claude\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\nDefault arguments passed to Claude Code:\n\n```\n-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\n```\n\nOverride with `agent_args` if needed:\n\n```\nstep implement {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  agent_args = \"-p --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n## Using an API Key Instead\n\nIf you prefer to use an API key rather than session reuse, set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in\nthe daemon's environment. Cloche passes it into containers automatically:\n\n```bash\nexport ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"sk-ant-...\"\ncloched &\n```\n\nThis works alongside session reuse — Claude Code will use the API key if no session\nis available.\n\n## Verifying the Setup\n\nRun a quick test workflow:\n\n```bash\ncloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Print hello world\"\n```\n\nCheck logs to confirm Claude Code is executing:\n\n```bash\ncloche logs <run-id>\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n**Claude Code not found in container**: Make sure your Dockerfile installs\n`@anthropic-ai/claude-code` via npm and that Node.js is available.\n\n**Authentication errors**: Run `claude` on the host to ensure your session is active.\nCloche copies `~/.claude/` at container creation time, so a stale or missing session\non the host means containers won't authenticate.\n\n**Permission errors on `~/.claude`**: Cloche runs `chown -R agent:agent` on the copied\nauth files at container startup. If you see permission errors, check that your\nDockerfile does not override the entrypoint.\n","numLines":119,"startLine":1,"totalLines":119}}}
