[2026-03-13T14:41:35Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TQUiMsxdg5gnwAGacmevRe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary of Authentication Files and Container Setup in Cloche\n\nBased on thorough analysis of the Go source code, here are the findings for all five questions:\n\n### 1. Authentication Files: Copied (Not Bind-Mounted)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 130-140)\n\nAuthentication files are **copied** into each container after creation, not bind-mounted:\n\n```go\n// Copy Claude auth files into container (each gets its own copy)\nif home, err := os.UserHomeDir(); err == nil {\n    claudeDir := home + \"/.claude\"\n    if _, err := os.Stat(claudeDir); err == nil {\n        exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"docker\", \"cp\", claudeDir, containerID+\":/home/agent/.claude\").Run()\n    }\n    claudeJSON := home + \"/.claude.json\"\n    if _, err := os.Stat(claudeJSON); err == nil {\n        exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"docker\", \"cp\", claudeJSON, containerID+\":/home/agent/.claude.json\").Run()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Files are copied from host `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` to container `/home/agent/.claude` and `/home/agent/.claude.json`\n- Copying (rather than mounting) ensures each container gets its own isolated copy, avoiding concurrent write conflicts\n- The operation is non-fatal if files don't exist (uses bare `.Run()` without error checking)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Environment Variables Passed to Containers\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 48-75)\n\n**Passed Environment Variables:**\n\n| Variable | How Passed | Details |\n|----------|-----------|---------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | `-e CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<value>` | Always passed from `cfg.RunID` |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | `-e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from host if set (line 52-54) |\n| Custom mounts | `-v host:container` | Via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` (comma-separated) |\n| Custom env vars | `-e KEY=VALUE` | Via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` (comma-separated) |\n\n**Code reference:**\n```go\n// Pass ANTHROPIC_API_KEY into container if set\nif key := os.Getenv(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"); key != \"\" {\n    args = append(args, \"-e\", \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\")\n}\n\n// Support extra volume mounts via CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS (comma-separated host:container pairs)\nif mounts := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS\"); mounts != \"\" {\n    for _, m := range strings.Split(mounts, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(m, \":\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-v\", m)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Support extra env vars via CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV (comma-separated KEY=VALUE pairs)\nif extraEnv := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV\"); extraEnv != \"\" {\n    for _, e := range strings.Split(extraEnv, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(e, \"=\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-e\", e)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Additional environment variables in-container:**\n\nInside running steps, these are also available:\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` (set by generic adapter for script steps)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Agent User Handling (chown, permissions)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 41-91)\n\nThe container runs as **root initially**, then switches to the **agent user** for actual work.\n\n**Wrapped Command (for default cloche-agent):**\n```bash\nchown -R agent:agent /workspace && \\\nchown -R agent:agent /home/agent/.claude /home/agent/.claude.json 2>/dev/null && \\\nrm -rf /workspace/.serena && \\\nf=/home/agent/.claude/settings.json && \\\n[ -f \"$f\" ] && sed -i '/\"enabledPlugins\"/,/}/d' \"$f\"; \\\nexec su agent -s /bin/sh -c <quoted-command>\n```\n\n**Key operations:**\n1. **Ownership transfer:** `chown -R agent:agent /workspace` — transfers workspace from root to agent user\n2. **Auth file permissions:** `chown -R agent:agent /home/agent/.claude /home/agent/.claude.json 2>/dev/null` — ensures agent owns auth files (errors suppressed with `2>/dev/null`)\n3. **Cleanup:** `rm -rf /workspace/.serena` — removes Serena MCP artifacts that slow agent onboarding\n4. **Plugin filtering:** Removes `\"enabledPlugins\"` section from `~/.claude/settings.json` to prevent wasted onboarding time\n5. **User switch:** `exec su agent -s /bin/sh -c <command>` — drops privileges to run workflow as non-root agent user\n\n**Base Dockerfile context:** `/workspace/docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile`\n```dockerfile\nRUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\nWORKDIR /workspace\nRUN chown agent:agent /workspace\nUSER agent\n```\n\nThe base image creates the agent user with home directory `/home/agent`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Known Agents and Default Arguments\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` (lines 19-51)\n\n**Known Agents:**\n\n```go\nvar defaultAgentArgs = map[string][]string{\n    \"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"},\n}\n```\n\n**Current Implementation:**\n- **Single known agent:** `claude`\n- **Default args for claude:** `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n- **Unknown agents:** Receive no default arguments (prompt passed via stdin only)\n\n**Command Resolution Priority** (from `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` lines 228-233):\n1. Step-level `agent_command` config\n2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }` config (for container workflows)\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n**Fallback Mechanism:**\n\nCommands can be comma-separated for fallback chains (e.g., `\"claude,gemini,codex\"`):\n\n```go\n// ParseCommands splits a comma-separated agent_command string\nfunc ParseCommands(s string) []string {\n    parts := strings.Split(s, \",\")\n    var cmds []string\n    for _, p := range parts {\n        p = strings.TrimSpace(p)\n        if p != \"\" {\n            cmds = append(cmds, p)\n        }\n    }\n    return cmds\n}\n```\n\n**Fallback Behavior** (from `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` lines 243-248):\n- **Command not found / failed to start** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n\n---\n\n### 5. CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS and CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV Mechanics\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 59-75)\n\n**CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS:**\n```go\nif mounts := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS\"); mounts != \"\" {\n    for _, m := range strings.Split(mounts, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(m, \":\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-v\", m)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n- **Format:** Comma-separated `host:container` pairs\n- **Validation:** Must contain `:` to be added\n- **Docker argument:** Each pair becomes a `-v` mount flag\n- **Example:** `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS=/data:/workspace/data,/config:/etc/config`\n\n**CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV:**\n```go\nif extraEnv := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV\"); extraEnv != \"\" {\n    for _, e := range strings.Split(extraEnv, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(e, \"=\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-e\", e)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n- **Format:** Comma-separated `KEY=VALUE` pairs\n- **Validation:** Must contain `=` to be added\n- **Docker argument:** Each pair becomes a `-e` env flag\n- **Example:** `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV=DEBUG=true,LOG_LEVEL=info,API_KEY=secret`\n\nBoth mechanisms allow host-side configuration without modifying workflows or container images.\n\n---\n\n## Files Analyzed\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` — Primary container setup logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` — Agent command resolution and fallback\n3. `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` — ContainerConfig interface definition\n4. `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` — In-container agent execution\n5. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` — Container launch coordination\n6. `/workspace/docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` — Base image setup\n7. `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` — User-facing documentation\n8. `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` — Agent entrypoint"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aeb1ae1d9b77a2853 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63397\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 88970</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ea6a4db-317b-4116-946b-dfa5f420f957","uuid":"e461be2c-bb04-4673-be8c-e5e283750e34","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the Go source code thoroughly to find how authentication files (~/.claude/, ~/.claude.json) are handled for containers. I need to know:\n\n1. Are they bind-mounted or copied? Look for \"claude\" in docker/container adapter code.\n2. What env vars are passed to containers (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV, etc.)?\n3. How is the \"agent\" user handled (chown, permissions)?\n4. What are the known agents and their default arguments? Look for agent command resolution code.\n5. How does CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS and CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV work?\n\nSearch in internal/adapters/, internal/domain/, cmd/ directories. Be very thorough - check all relevant files.","agentId":"aeb1ae1d9b77a2853","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary of Authentication Files and Container Setup in Cloche\n\nBased on thorough analysis of the Go source code, here are the findings for all five questions:\n\n### 1. Authentication Files: Copied (Not Bind-Mounted)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 130-140)\n\nAuthentication files are **copied** into each container after creation, not bind-mounted:\n\n```go\n// Copy Claude auth files into container (each gets its own copy)\nif home, err := os.UserHomeDir(); err == nil {\n    claudeDir := home + \"/.claude\"\n    if _, err := os.Stat(claudeDir); err == nil {\n        exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"docker\", \"cp\", claudeDir, containerID+\":/home/agent/.claude\").Run()\n    }\n    claudeJSON := home + \"/.claude.json\"\n    if _, err := os.Stat(claudeJSON); err == nil {\n        exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"docker\", \"cp\", claudeJSON, containerID+\":/home/agent/.claude.json\").Run()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Files are copied from host `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` to container `/home/agent/.claude` and `/home/agent/.claude.json`\n- Copying (rather than mounting) ensures each container gets its own isolated copy, avoiding concurrent write conflicts\n- The operation is non-fatal if files don't exist (uses bare `.Run()` without error checking)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Environment Variables Passed to Containers\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 48-75)\n\n**Passed Environment Variables:**\n\n| Variable | How Passed | Details |\n|----------|-----------|---------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | `-e CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<value>` | Always passed from `cfg.RunID` |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | `-e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from host if set (line 52-54) |\n| Custom mounts | `-v host:container` | Via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` (comma-separated) |\n| Custom env vars | `-e KEY=VALUE` | Via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` (comma-separated) |\n\n**Code reference:**\n```go\n// Pass ANTHROPIC_API_KEY into container if set\nif key := os.Getenv(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"); key != \"\" {\n    args = append(args, \"-e\", \"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\")\n}\n\n// Support extra volume mounts via CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS (comma-separated host:container pairs)\nif mounts := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS\"); mounts != \"\" {\n    for _, m := range strings.Split(mounts, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(m, \":\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-v\", m)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Support extra env vars via CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV (comma-separated KEY=VALUE pairs)\nif extraEnv := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV\"); extraEnv != \"\" {\n    for _, e := range strings.Split(extraEnv, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(e, \"=\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-e\", e)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Additional environment variables in-container:**\n\nInside running steps, these are also available:\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` (set by generic adapter for script steps)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Agent User Handling (chown, permissions)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 41-91)\n\nThe container runs as **root initially**, then switches to the **agent user** for actual work.\n\n**Wrapped Command (for default cloche-agent):**\n```bash\nchown -R agent:agent /workspace && \\\nchown -R agent:agent /home/agent/.claude /home/agent/.claude.json 2>/dev/null && \\\nrm -rf /workspace/.serena && \\\nf=/home/agent/.claude/settings.json && \\\n[ -f \"$f\" ] && sed -i '/\"enabledPlugins\"/,/}/d' \"$f\"; \\\nexec su agent -s /bin/sh -c <quoted-command>\n```\n\n**Key operations:**\n1. **Ownership transfer:** `chown -R agent:agent /workspace` — transfers workspace from root to agent user\n2. **Auth file permissions:** `chown -R agent:agent /home/agent/.claude /home/agent/.claude.json 2>/dev/null` — ensures agent owns auth files (errors suppressed with `2>/dev/null`)\n3. **Cleanup:** `rm -rf /workspace/.serena` — removes Serena MCP artifacts that slow agent onboarding\n4. **Plugin filtering:** Removes `\"enabledPlugins\"` section from `~/.claude/settings.json` to prevent wasted onboarding time\n5. **User switch:** `exec su agent -s /bin/sh -c <command>` — drops privileges to run workflow as non-root agent user\n\n**Base Dockerfile context:** `/workspace/docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile`\n```dockerfile\nRUN useradd -m -s /bin/bash agent\nWORKDIR /workspace\nRUN chown agent:agent /workspace\nUSER agent\n```\n\nThe base image creates the agent user with home directory `/home/agent`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Known Agents and Default Arguments\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` (lines 19-51)\n\n**Known Agents:**\n\n```go\nvar defaultAgentArgs = map[string][]string{\n    \"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"},\n}\n```\n\n**Current Implementation:**\n- **Single known agent:** `claude`\n- **Default args for claude:** `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`\n- **Unknown agents:** Receive no default arguments (prompt passed via stdin only)\n\n**Command Resolution Priority** (from `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` lines 228-233):\n1. Step-level `agent_command` config\n2. Workflow-level `container { agent_command }` config (for container workflows)\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n**Fallback Mechanism:**\n\nCommands can be comma-separated for fallback chains (e.g., `\"claude,gemini,codex\"`):\n\n```go\n// ParseCommands splits a comma-separated agent_command string\nfunc ParseCommands(s string) []string {\n    parts := strings.Split(s, \",\")\n    var cmds []string\n    for _, p := range parts {\n        p = strings.TrimSpace(p)\n        if p != \"\" {\n            cmds = append(cmds, p)\n        }\n    }\n    return cmds\n}\n```\n\n**Fallback Behavior** (from `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` lines 243-248):\n- **Command not found / failed to start** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n\n---\n\n### 5. CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS and CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV Mechanics\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` (lines 59-75)\n\n**CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS:**\n```go\nif mounts := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS\"); mounts != \"\" {\n    for _, m := range strings.Split(mounts, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(m, \":\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-v\", m)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n- **Format:** Comma-separated `host:container` pairs\n- **Validation:** Must contain `:` to be added\n- **Docker argument:** Each pair becomes a `-v` mount flag\n- **Example:** `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS=/data:/workspace/data,/config:/etc/config`\n\n**CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV:**\n```go\nif extraEnv := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV\"); extraEnv != \"\" {\n    for _, e := range strings.Split(extraEnv, \",\") {\n        if strings.Contains(e, \"=\") {\n            args = append(args, \"-e\", e)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n- **Format:** Comma-separated `KEY=VALUE` pairs\n- **Validation:** Must contain `=` to be added\n- **Docker argument:** Each pair becomes a `-e` env flag\n- **Example:** `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV=DEBUG=true,LOG_LEVEL=info,API_KEY=secret`\n\nBoth mechanisms allow host-side configuration without modifying workflows or container images.\n\n---\n\n## Files Analyzed\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` — Primary container setup logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` — Agent command resolution and fallback\n3. `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` — ContainerConfig interface definition\n4. `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` — In-container agent execution\n5. `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` — Container launch coordination\n6. `/workspace/docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` — Base image setup\n7. `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` — User-facing documentation\n8. `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` — Agent entrypoint"}],"totalDurationMs":88970,"totalTokens":63397,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1854,"cache_read_input_tokens":59088,"output_tokens":2452,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"ser